---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Dental Hygienists Matter" description="Evidence-based information on Virginia dental workforce legislation affecting preventive care." >
  <section class="grid">
    <div class="col-7">
      <h1>Protect standards of care in preventive dentistry.</h1>
      <p class="muted">
        We support safe, evidence-based access to care. We oppose legislative shortcuts that risk confusing patients and lowering the standard of preventive dental treatment.
      </p>
      <div class="btns">
        <a class="btn btn--danger" href="/the-bills">Read about SB 178 &amp; HB 970</a>
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/take-action">Take action</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/sources">Sources</a>
      </div>

      <h2>What Route B does (in plain English)</h2>
      <div class="panel">
        <p>
          <strong>Workforce expansion route B</strong> creates a new certification for <strong>"preventive/preventative dental assistants"</strong> and authorizes them to perform
          <strong>limited scaling/polishing</strong> (described publicly as “above-the-gumline” cleanings) under dentist supervision.
        </p>
        <p class="muted">
          Supporters describe this as a way to increase throughput. Opponents argue it risks incomplete care and increased disease progression by normalizing partial cleanings.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="col-5">
      <div class="panel callout callout--danger">
        <h2>Key concern</h2>
        <p>
          A “cleaning” that focuses only above the gumline can create a false sense of completion and may delay identification and treatment of periodontal disease.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel" style="margin-top: 14px;">
        <h2>What we’re asking for</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Do not pass</strong> SB 178 / HB 970 as written.</li>
          <li>If legislation advances, add <strong>strong guardrails</strong>: clear patient eligibility criteria, independent competency verification, transparency/informed consent, reporting, and a sunset clause.</li>
          <li>Prioritize <strong>retention</strong> and <strong>workplace solutions</strong> to address hygiene access.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Start here</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="col-12 panel">
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/patient-safety">Patient safety and standard-of-care concerns</a></li>
          <li><a href="/better-solutions">Better ways to expand access without lowering standards</a></li>
          <li><a href="/take-action">A simple script to contact legislators</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
